cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with the problem of covering a d-dimensional space with sensors, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algorithms and analysis of their performance makes it relevant to the data structures and algorithms category (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of the tradeoff between the sensing radius and the total movement. The use of simulations and discussion of results makes it relevant to the systems and control category (cs.SY), and the optimization of the total movement makes it relevant to the numerical analysis category (cs.NA).
